params._numTokens: The number of tokens to purchase

params._intakeCap: The maximum amount of purchaseToken we wish to receive
params._limits: The maximum and minimum amount of tokens a user can purchase (as percent of total sold)
params._periodLength: How long in seconds each period of the sale should last
params._startingPrice: The sale price to start at, expressed in units of _purchaseToken per token being sold, as a WAD
params._stoppable: Whether or not the sale can be paused or stopped prior to completion
params._targets: The target and maximum number of tokens to sell per period
params._times: The times to start and end the sale
params._tokens: The tokens we are selling and buying. Use 0x0 to buy Ether
params._windowSize: Characteristic number of periods that should be used for the moving average. In the long-term, 86% of the weighting will be in this window size. The higher the number, the slower the price will be to adjust

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params._beneficiary: The beneficiary to receive sale proceeds
